$ mongorestore --username adminUser --password pass123 --authenticationDatabase admin --db exampleDB dump/exampleDB


connect in mongo protected with password
mongo --username <your username> --password <your password>
show dbs

backup db
mongodump --host=10.10.10.59 --port=27017 --db=<Database> --authenticationDatabase=admin -u=<Username> -p=<Password>
mongodump --db=<Database> --collection=<Collection> --out=<Directory Location> --authenticationDatabase=admin -u=<Username> -p=<Password> --gzip

- How compress folder in linux
tar -zcvf <file name>.tar.gz <directory name>
-z Compress archive using gzip program in Linux or Unix
-c Create archive on Linux
-v Verbose i.e display progress while creating archive
-f Archive File name


Site with good commands
https://www.bmc.com/blogs/mongodb-mongodump/
https://www.bmc.com/blogs/mongodb-mongorestore/

#extract tar files
tar -xvzf mywebsitebackup.tar.gz -C /path/to/directory


